records.addlTxt: Signed bond filed with the court.

TOTAL BOND COVERS ALL FILES 20CF555 & 22CF271
Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  Defendant will not possess any guns or other weapons.   Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any co-actor(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  CO-ACTOR(S)/RESIDENCE(S):NO CONTACT WITH CO-DEFENDANT *ERIC HOLLEN.  Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.

2:30pm Court in session

Defendant Sarah Hollen present in court, late, with attorney Steve Compton. James Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
State has filed a new complaint for felony bail jumping. Atty Compton acknowledges receipt of that complaint. 
State asking for cash component to bond. 
Response by Atty Compton that Deft has no means to post any cash at this time. 

Court sets $5,000.00 signature bond
Same conditions as prior bond.

Court notes that Deft has never signed her bond. 
Court cancels bail forfeiture hearing.  

Atty Compton would like to have a waiver of preliminary hearing today on the newest file. 
Court goes off the record for Atty Compton to go over paperwork with Deft. 

2:42pm Court back on the record. 

Appearances remain. Atty Compton provides waiver of preliminary hearing paperwork to Court. 
Court has colloquy with Deft. Response by Counsel and defendant to Court's questions.  Court finds defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily waives his right to a preliminary hearing and binds the defendant over. 

Warrant quashed.

2:43pm Court in recess
